"meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Old French, Anglo-Norman French, and Middle English personal name <i>Neel</i>, <i>Nele</i>, <i>Nihel</i>, <i>Niel</i>, itself derived from the Latin name <i>Nigellus</i> (a diminutive of Latin <i>niger</i> ‘black’), originally a nickname for someone with black hair or a dark complexion. The name was very common among Normans and was brought to England at the time of the Norman Conquest. There has been considerable confusion with the Irish and Scottish Gaelic name <i>Niall</i> (see   Neil  ); the two names are now pronounced identically. It is theoretically possible that in Normandy, where the personal name was popular, that it was also used for Old Norse <i>Njáll</i>, but this is difficult to prove. <i>Njáll</i> was adopted from the Irish Gaelic personal name <i>Niall</i> by Vikings in Ireland, who took it back to Iceland and Norway, but whether the Vikings also took <i>Njáll</i> to Normandy and to the northwest of England, is an open question, which cannot be settled on the available evidence.","English: alternatively from the Middle English personal name <i>Nele</i>, a variant of   Nell   as a pet form of <i>Elias</i> (see   Ellis  ). Compare   Nelson  ,   Nielson  .","Scottish and Irish: shortened form of   McNeal   (see   McNeil  )."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mr Neel de Saint-Sauveur was born about 1180, in France as the son of Roger de St. Sauveur. He had at least 1 daughter with Cécile du Port de FormignyY."},"et":{"about 1180–":"umbes 1180–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1085–Female":"1085–Surnud","1125–Female":"1125–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1125":"1125","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1085":"1085","1180":"1180","of France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1180–":"noin 1180–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1085–Female":"1085–Kuollut","1125–Female":"1125–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1125":"1125","about 1180":"noin 1180","1085":"1085","1180":"1180","of France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1180–":"environ 1180–Décédé","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","1085–Female":"1085–Décédée","1125–Female":"1125–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1125":"1125","about 1180":"environ 1180","1085":"1085","1180":"1180","of France":"France","lifeSummary":"Mr Neel de Saint-Sauveur est né environ 1180, à France, fils de Roger de St. Sauveur. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Cécile du Port de FormignyY."},"de":{"about 1180–":"um 1180–Verstorben","1180–Male":"1180–Verstorben","1085–Female":"1085–Verstorben","1125–Female":"1125–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1125":"1125","about 1180":"um 1180","1085":"1085","1180":"1180","of France":"Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Mr Neel de Saint-Sauveur wurde um 1180 in Frankreich, als Sohn von Roger de St. Sauveur geboren. Er hatte mit Cécile du Port de FormignyY mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"about 1180–":"about 1180–Desede","1180–Male":"1180–Desede","1085–Female":"1085–Desede","1125–Female":"1125–Desede","–Male":"Desede","1125":"1125","about 1180":"about 1180","1085":"1085","1180":"1180","of France":"France"},"hu":{"about 1180–":"1180 körül–elhunyt","1180–Male":"1180–elhunyt","1085–Female":"1085–elhunyt","1125–Female":"1125–elhunyt","–Male":"elhunyt","1125":"1125","about 1180":"1180 körül","1085":"1085","1180":"1180","of France":"Franciaország"},"id":{"about 1180–":"sekitar 1180–Telah Meninggal","1180–Male":"1180–